description: Close to the Palace of Versailles, the Sun King's doctor's farm. Charm, completely renovated and equipped. Beams over 550 years old, 70 cm thick walls, 5.50 m high ceilings, facing south. Duplex 70 m2 furnished with taste, bathroom in aged marble, wc. 3 large Vélux style roof windows, very bright, triple exposure, 1 bedroom on the mezzanine, living room. Private garden with stream. Near equestrian center, Saint-Nom-la-Bretèche golf course.

Notre-Dame Richaud district, 2 rooms furnished completely renovated, 27.78 m2 + 1.30 m2.
Near the Hoche and La Bruyère high schools, universities, ISIPCA, the school of architecture, the administrative and judicial city, the market, the Castle and its park.
Secure building, intercom, armored door with peephole. 2nd floor, no lift.
Entrance, living room with view on the Richaud district, quiet bedroom overlooking the courtyard, fitted kitchen open to living room, bathroom with walk-in shower.
Equipment: 4 * refrigerator, hotplates, extractor hood, oven and microwave, vacuum cleaner, Queen size bed, sofa bed for third bed.
Additional equipment: dishwasher, washing machine, TV, numerous kitchen utensils and small appliances (Dolce Gusto coffee maker, kettle, toaster, iron, etc.), large reception crockery. Linens provided.
Possibility to park a bicycle. Well connected :
- 4 minutes walk from Versailles Rive Droite station (direct line La Défense, St Lazare)
- 10 minutes walk from Versailles Rive Gauche station (direct Saint-Michel)

Located rue Hoche, in the heart of the historic and dynamic district of Notre Dame, 5 min walk from the Palace, 5 min walk from Versailles Rive-Droite train station and 10 min walk from Versailles Rive-Gauche train station.
This charming little house is located in a beautiful 18th century building and is close to all the shops on Rue de la Paroisse. Very calm and bright, its 5 windows overlook a paved courtyard. It has just been completely renovated with quality materials (solid oak parquet, Ressource paints, new high-end frames).
On the ground floor: the tiled entrance continues with a beautiful oak staircase giving access to the living rooms.
The living / dining room opens onto an open kitchen (new furniture and appliances: oven, gas hob, fridge freezer, extractor, microwave, Nespresso coffee machine). Crockery provided.
Living room: sofa and new furniture (coffee table, armchairs, dining room table, chairs) Samsung TV.
Single room with 140 bed, plenty of storage space and old marble fireplace.
Bathroom with wc and washing machine.
Linens provided (duvet, ears, sheets, towels, tea towels ..).
Individual gas boiler.
The double glazed windows have all been changed.

Clear view, bright, sunny, double exposure South street and North courtyard, calm.
Collective central heating, comfort, economical (Charges including heating, water) double glazing,
Entrance with storage, separate fitted kitchen (with crockery, stove, fridge, freezer, microwave, washing machine)
bathroom with window, large Italian shower, storage, wall mounted clothes rack.
Separate toilet, with storage, and storage space with wardrobe and shelves.
Living room with convertible sofa and storage, and dining area
bedroom facing courtyard, with storage and office area.
Small quiet joint ownership. 2nd floor of 3.
